					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Shibole ha-leḳeṭ and Hilkhot isur ve-heter by Zidkiyahu figlio di Abraham ha-Rofe Anav.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="236v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Shibole ha-leḳeṭ</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שבלי הלקט</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/17078692">Zidkiyahu figlio di Abraham, ha-Rofe, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/17078692">צדקיה בן אברהם, הרופא, מרומה</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The manuscripts is incomplete, lacking several portions appearing in the standard edition of the work.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Shibole_haleket_1987"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="237r" to="363v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hilkhot isur ve-heter</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">הלכות איסור והיתר</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Zidkiyahu figlio di Abraham, ha-Rofe, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">צדקיה בן אברהם, הרופא, מרומה<addName>http://viaf.org/viaf/17078692</addName>
								</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Add MS 26918, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">529</ref>.</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>Breaks off in the middle of the 113th paragraph.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>363 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>270</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>363 folios (+ 4 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Folios 1 and 2 are modern paper flyleaves.</p>
									<p>The manuscript has two different foliations, one in the Hebrew order of folios, the other in the Latin order of folios.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>41 quires of mostly 10 leaves each, numbered on the first leaf, in the left-hand upper corner. </p>
									<p>Wanting quires no. 1-4, the first leaf of the 5th quire and the last leaf of the 41st quire.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Incomplete at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Three leaves cancelled after folio 148, and two after folio 234.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="33" writtenLines="33">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. </p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written outside the ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires, partially preserved.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Latin notes on the lower half of folio 236v: 'ex Bibliotheca, non J.B. Colbert, sed <name type="person" role="owner">Caroli Joachimi Colbert</name> Episcopi Montispessulani, quae A.D. <date calendar="Gregorian">1740 </date>publica subhastationis lege fuit dividenda.'</p>
							<p>An English description of the manuscript, pasted on the paper flyleaves at the beginning of the volume, folios 1v, 2r.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Brown leather, blind tooled, with Colbert's coat of arms on the upper and lower cover.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'R. Zidkiah ben Abraham. Shebile Halleket. Hebraice. Mus. Brit. Iure Emptionis. 15,437.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
